article:
Double}} 'The Double', in association football, is the achievement of winning a
country's top tier division and its primary cup competition in the same season.
It can also mean beating a team both home and away in the same league season, a
feat often noted as doing the double over a particular side.

The first club to achieve a double was Preston North End in 1889, winning the FA
Cup and the Football League in the inaugural season of the league.
